Subject: Re: [VB] was soundproofing, now insulating....

Mine is done much the same way.  One tip - take the bus for a spin now 
to check
for squeaks.   The silver bubble wrap held in place with aluminium tape 
will find
a way to rub, and you don't want to have to remove your interior and 
paneling to
reposition a piece of bubble foam.

Tom.

On 2011/03/19 15:34, Kevin Guarnotta wrote:
> I've posted some pics of the insulation install on my '65. I used the silver
> bubble wrap stuff. As suggested, I came up with a way to make a spacer
> between the previously installed soundproofing. I took strips of the
> insulation stuff, and doubled it back on itself, and then glued that in
> place. Then the insulation went over that. Now I have a small air-gap
> between the insulation and the exterior layers of soundproofing/shell of the
> bus. The top layers of insulation are held in place with some aluminum tape.
